Replace this PR's current approach with a MINIMAL cursor fix. The user explicitly wants to minimize config. The branch currently contains an over-engineered fix in home/desktop.nix (a `hyprcursor.enable = true;` line plus a large `xdg.dataFile."icons/Bibata-Modern-Ice-hyprcursor"` derivation that runs hyprcursor-util to generate a hyprcursor theme). REMOVE all of that and use the minimal approach below instead.

WHY (context for good comments):
- classic-laddie runs Hyprland 0.55, which defaults to hyprcursor. The configured cursor (bibata-cursors / Bibata-Modern-Ice) ships ONLY as an XCursor theme, so Hyprland finds no hyprcursor theme and falls back to a generic default cursor — this is the 'cursor changed appearance' regression the user noticed after a reboot activated a system upgrade.
- The Bibata XCursor theme is ALREADY installed and on XCURSOR_PATH (verified at /etc/profiles/per-user/patrick/share/icons/Bibata-Modern-Ice/cursors, 145 cursors). Nothing needs to be generated.
- The real gap is that XCURSOR_THEME is not exported anywhere in the session, so even Hyprland's XCursor fallback has no theme name to load. The minimal fix is to tell Hyprland to use XCursor and point it at the already-installed Bibata theme — no derivation, no hyprcursor theme generation.

CHANGES:

1) home/desktop.nix — REVERT this PR's additions. Restore the `home.pointerCursor` block to exactly:
    home.pointerCursor = {
      gtk.enable = true;
      # x11.enable = true;
      package = pkgs.bibata-cursors;
      name = "Bibata-Modern-Ice";
      size = 24;
    };
   i.e. delete the `hyprcursor.enable = true;` line, delete the hyprcursor explanatory comment added by this PR, and delete the ENTIRE `xdg.dataFile."icons/Bibata-Modern-Ice-hyprcursor".source = pkgs.runCommand ...` block. home/desktop.nix must end up identical to its state on the main branch (no net change from this file in the final PR diff). Keep home.pointerCursor as-is — it is still useful for GTK apps.

2) home/hyprland.nix — apply the minimal fix. In the existing cursor block (currently:
      cursor = {
        no_hardware_cursors = true;
      };
), add `enable_hyprcursor = false;` so Hyprland uses XCursor instead of hyprcursor. Then export the cursor theme name+size to the Hyprland session so XCursor resolves Bibata. Prefer Hyprland's own env mechanism (the hyprland home-manager module's `settings.env`, a list of "KEY,VALUE" strings): add "XCURSOR_THEME,Bibata-Modern-Ice" and "XCURSOR_SIZE,24". IMPORTANT: if an `env` list already exists in the hyprland settings, APPEND these two entries to it — do not create a second `env` key or clobber existing entries. Add a brief comment explaining why (Hyprland 0.55 defaults to hyprcursor; Bibata is xcursor-only; disabling hyprcursor + naming the theme restores the pre-upgrade cursor with minimal config).

CONSTRAINTS:
- Keep it minimal — the net PR diff should be roughly: home/desktop.nix unchanged vs main, and only a few added lines in home/hyprland.nix.
- Follow repo conventions (AGENTS.md): Nix, 2-space indent, declarative. No direct commits to main.

VALIDATION (before finalizing):
- Build the host: `nix build .#nixosConfigurations.classic-laddie.config.system.build.toplevel` — must succeed.
- Prove the settings land in the generated Hyprland config: locate the built hyprland.conf in the toplevel (or nix eval the hyprland settings) and confirm it contains `enable_hyprcursor = false` (or cursor:enable_hyprcursor = false) AND both env lines `env = XCURSOR_THEME,Bibata-Modern-Ice` and `env = XCURSOR_SIZE,24`. Report exactly how you confirmed.
- Confirm home/desktop.nix no longer contains 'hyprcursor' or 'xdg.dataFile' (grep it) and matches main.
- Run any pre-commit hooks / fast flake check if present; fix failures.
- Do NOT run switch/activate on the running system.

Also UPDATE the PR title and description to reflect the new minimal approach: title something like 'home/hyprland: restore Bibata cursor via XCursor (minimal, no hyprcursor theme gen)'. In the description, explain the regression (Hyprland 0.55 hyprcursor default + xcursor-only Bibata + unset XCURSOR_THEME => default-cursor fallback) and that this replaces an earlier hyprcursor-generation approach with a 2-line XCursor fix per the maintainer's request to minimize config. Note the user should re-login (or run `hyprctl setcursor Bibata-Modern-Ice 24`) after rebuild for it to take effect.

